Package: LandComp
Title: a package for analysing landscape composition and structure at
    multiple scales
Version: 0.0.0.9000
Authors@R: c(
    person("Krisztina Dóra", "Konrád", , "konrad.krisztina@ecolres.hu", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-4414-8766")),
    person("Ákos", "Bede-Fazekas", , "bfakos@ecolres.hu", role = "aut",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-2905-338X"))
  )
Description: Changes of landscape diversity and structure can be detected
    soon if relying on landscape class combinations and analysing patterns
    at multiple scales. LandComp provides such an opportunity, based on
    Juhász-Nagy's functions. Functions can handle multilayered data.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Suggests: 
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    testthat
Encoding: UTF-8
Language: En
Requirements regarding the input: binary data contained by a regular
    square or hexagonal grid, and the grid should have projected
    coordinates.
